OL,4,BRacism in football: Serie A clubs
OL,5,Bpledge to combat abuse in Italy
OL,6, All 20 Serie A clubs have made a united
OL,7, pledge to combat Italian football's
OL,8, "serious problem" with racism because
OL,9, there is no more "time to waste".
OL,11,FThe top-flight clubs said they could
OL,12,F"no longer stay silent" after several
OL,13,Frecent incidents in which Serie A
OL,14,Fplayers have been racially abused.
OL,16,F"It's a problem we have not done enough
OL,17,Fto combat over the years," the clubs
OL,18,Fsaid in an open letter on Friday.
OL,20,F"We, the undersigned clubs, are united
OL,21,Fby our desire for serious change."
